name: Western Montana Photography
description:
Welcome!

This group is free and open to photographers of all levels of experience in Western Montana including Kalispell, Missoula, Helena and beyond, as well as short-term visitors to the area. The purpose is to promote photographic expression and learning through shared experiences and knowledge. We hope to cover a wide range of topics during in-person discussions and photo walks. Add your photos to the site and see them featured on the Home Page!

The good folks at RMSP have published their 2015-2016 Evening Lecture Series calendar.

name: The Original Missoula Entrepreneur Meetup Group
description: A group for entrepreneurs and self-employed people in the Missoula area.

name: Missoula Hiking Meetup
description: It appears that every hiking group in Missoula is inactive as of 2016, this group is for anyone interested in going on regular day hikes around the Missoula area. This group is a great way to meet new people and make new friends in the Missoula area. Dogs are not only welcome, but encouraged (so long as they like people and getting attention). As this group grows I'd love to diversify hikes to include activities: Hikes & Brews, Hikes & Hammocks, Hikes & Bootcamp (any aspiring local trainers want to join us?), etc.

name: Montana Programmers
description:
Montana Programmers is a rapidly growing community of programmers.

Our goal is to build a fun and rewarding network of coders from all walks of life, languages, backgrounds, industries, and skill levels. We strive to provide a place where both an expert and a novice can learn cool new things. Share and grow in the art of programming.

We have groups in Kalispell (59901), Polson (59860), Missoula (59801), Bozeman (59715), Helena (59620), Great Falls (59401) and Billings (59102).

Every month we try to schedule at least one meetup in each town. We also hold mini meets or drinkups, which are generally pretty informal.

The group is open to everyone. Just pick an event on the calendar and RSVP.

See you at the next meetup!

Find Us On Facebook

Find Us On Google+

Find Us On Twitter

Watch past Meetups on Vimeo

name: Missoula Tango
description:
To enjoy Argentine tango through social dances, practicas (practices), classes, lessons, workshops, guerilla tango (out and about town and different kinds of music and such!), tango flash mobs, and general fun community building together around tango.

Also on the web at: http://www.tangomissoula.com/

And Facebook: Missoula TangoOpen Group

name: GDG Missoula
description:
The Missoula Google Developer Group (GDG) brings together people who are interested in technology and software in Missoula. If you are looking for employment, you can make connections to tech companies in the area and make a good impression. If you're looking to hire, you can get to know developers in person. Either way you get to hear about cool new technology and share some food and drinks with like minded people. 

If you or someone you know might be interested in presenting or showing something that they built recently send a message to one of the organizers or bring it up and the next meeting.

We try to get together on the first Thursday of each month. 

The website is http://gdg-missoula.github.io/

name: Missoula 50+
description:
We are a group of people - singles and couples - over 50 who want to enjoy the company of others, meet new friends and have some fun! This isn't a "singles" group!! Couples are welcome too! We'll explore all Missoula and Western Montana has to offer, from socializing to travel. Whether you've lived in the area for many years, or are new, please join us for some adventure, laughs and lasting friendships. As a group we are open for suggestions of new activities. 

If you have been enjoying our group and would like to see it continue on this forum, please consider a donation of whatever amount you are comfortable with be it $1, $5 or $10 to the organizer. 

 Meetup charges approximately $15.00 per month to provide us with our website forum. The Organizer does this by paying from his personal funds and then relying on the generosity of our members to pitch in donations.He has opted not to put up a “chip in” button on our site because of the “service fees” charged, which reduce the amount of the donation our group receives.

name: Wagg'n Nation: Come. Sit. Stay awhile.
description:
We are your all-in-one community for you and your canine family member. You can stay and play, boarding while you are away, receive dog grooming, visit with a vet, and much more in a safe, engaging environment.

As a Wagg'n Nation member you will enjoy an exclusive community of responsible pet parents who are passionate about their family's physical, social and mental health. Multiple dog discounts are available.
- Off-leash, indoor/outdoor play area for dog and family
- Agility training area
- Free social groups for you and your dog
- Free educational talks by behavioral specialists
- Free dog bathing area
- Free industrial washers and dryers
- Human comforts of coffee bar, free Wi-Fi, big screen TVs and lounge area
- Receive our newsletter, Paw Print, featuring articles to improve your dog's health
- Member only significant discounts off of Wagg'n services and products
- Handicap and ADA accessible for dogs and humans.

We will be opening boarding facilities first. We are on track to meet our goal of opening in May. Our location is the corner of Broadway and Palmer (2600 Charlo). Missoula, MT.

name: Missoula Entrepreneurship Meetup
description: The Missoula Entrepreneurship Meetup is a member of the Collaborative Entrepreneurship Network, a global ecosystem of investors and entrepreneurs working to help early stage startups. As investors and former entrepreneurs ourselves, we believe that both innovators and investors can learn from each other and make meaningful connections and relationships, but that too often entrepreneurs who aren’t already well connected have quite a hurdle to cross to make their first connection. At CEN events, we help early stage startups present to and connect with local investors, collaborate with industry thought leaders, brainstorm with each other, and share advice and resources.

name: Missoula Swing Dancing Parties, Practices, Lessons, Meetup
description: To Swing Dance everywhere possible including: parties, practices, classes, lessons, workshops, performances etc. Every form of swing dance lover of every age is welcome! To share opportunities to dance where anyone can feel comfortable, included and accepted.

name: New Friends Group
description:
This group exists to connect soon-to-be friends in the Missoula area. All are welcome to join us, whether you are new to the area or you have been here most of your life. If you are looking for a group of friendly folks to join for hikes, festivals, farmers markets, dinner parties, river floats, camping trips, games nights, BBQs, or any of the other million fun things to do in Missoula then this is the group for you!

This is primarily an adults-only group, but we do have events where children are welcome. Please check in with the event’s host before RSVP’ing your kids to attend.

We love it when members suggest events, so keep your ideas coming! There are only two things to keep in mind: 1) No marketing events where people are going to be asked to buy a product or service, and 2) The organizers reserve the right to decline event ideas that we believe pose unnecessary safety hazards to our members. Everything else is fair game, and some of our best events have been suggested by members.

We look forward to meeting you soon!

name: Missoula Backpackers
description:
Come share a passion for backpacking with us

This is a group for those who enjoy backpacking and sharing this passion with others.  These backpacking trips can be anything from a couple miles into an alpine lake to a multi-day loop.

The trips will require backpacks, tents, sleeping bags and other gear/food you need to keep fed, warm, and dry.  This group practices Leave No Trace along with trying to leave the areas better than we found it. 

Each individual is responsible for their own safety and to come equipped with the proper items for a successful trip.

Trail trained dogs are permitted on most trips. 

This group is not only for seasoned backpackers but for those who have an interest in learning more.  Along with the backpacking trips there will also be gatherings (at a brewery or distillery).  This will be a great opportunity for everyone to socialize and meet before embarking on a trip. 

Above all, this is a group of like-minded individuals that are here to have an enjoyable time.  We have two rules.  The first is Respect.  Respect for one another along with respect for Mother Nature.  Failure to follow this rule will get you banned from the group.  

The second rule is to Hike Your Hike.  Meaning that these events are during your free time and for your enjoyment.  If your hike involves photography then feel free to stop as often as you like.  If you want to pull off and fish a lake on the way, then feel free.  If you hike a faster pace then do not let us slow you down.  We are all adults and will reassemble at designated locations.

Please take a moment to review the Terms and Acknowledgement page listed here.  By signing up/RSVPing yes to any event you are confirming that you have reviewed and accept these terms.

Otherwise thank you so much for joining the group and we look forward to meeting you!

name: Casual Biking Group Missoula
description: I want to do casual rides, on pavement/dirt/single track. Preferably with food and maybe drink interspersed after!
